{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"41f2e65f-e31d-45e1-a3c3-38dbe2a18fd9","content":"The problem is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01SG2yoY2ESgdfZ5QPVKxDu7","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HWfUphJQVabThoFR1vKeU4","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-14c13d49d964481799ce992421a4af03/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-14c13d49d964481799ce992421a4af03/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"0bcfddbc-3723-42f9-ba41-17166d99bcbe","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed **before** them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":384,"requestId":"EC1E:1FB596:AB96AF:D4E568:6A0128D6"},"id":"9125c8f2-6df5-4fa4-b086-f3b18ec1a85b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:54.836Z","parentId":"47d745eb-974f-4559-8bb9-a8ff8697d94b"}
